The paper discusses the use of modern information retrieval and text mining methods in an adaptive human-computer interface, which suggests that it belongs to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of an evolutionary algorithm for adaptive navigation, which falls under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of text mining methods and the concept of a Knowledge Map suggest that the paper may also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of real-time collaborative feedback analysis, which suggests that it may belong to the Deep Learning (cs.DL) sub-category. Finally, the use of an adaptive algorithm for navigation suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
